<item>
            <title>[CXF-5016] ArithmeticException on ResponseTimeCounterMBean.getAvgResponseTime() after counter reset()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-5016</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A JMX client program such as monitoring platform (Nagios plugin, HypericHQ, ...) retrieve metrics like AvgResponseTime per minute.&lt;br/&gt;
One way to retrieve data is to fetch value every minute and reset counter immediately after.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if no calls to the service has been made since last reset, you get an ArithmeticException &quot;divide by zero&quot; when calling ResponseTimeCounterMBean.getAvgResponseTime()&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest handling this case by returning 0 or -1 instead, thus avoiding exception and alarming stacktrace on the monitoring client side.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;ResponseTimeCounter.getAvgResponseTime()&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Number&lt;/span&gt; getAvgResponseTime() {        
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (_invocations.get() == 0) {
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; -1; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// avoid divide by 0;
&lt;/span&gt;  }
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt;)(totalHandlingTime / invocations.get());
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

</description>
